si.t: The vehicle's actual license plate as registered in the system and as shown in the tag image.

The LPR system's common interpretation of the vehicle license plate that may contain characters different from the actual tag. In most cases, it is followed or preceded by a Parent LPR. If no Parent is found, always check the image to verify the correct tag and search for it in the system. Once found, add the interpreted as the Child and assign its Parent.
Both zero in the Residential and Visitor Count. Accurate interpretation of an unregistered tag as verified through the tag image. Tag is not found in the system. (NR-Not Registered)
License plate is not found in the system. Interpretation contains characters different from the actual tag as verified through the tag image.

For interpretations that did not go through because of the following reasons: wrong angle, vehicle markings or background distractors were captured instead of the plate, and tags with 4-8 characters but only 3-1 characters were interpreted. (do not add this in the system)

The vehicle's license plate is obstructed or covered by something preventing you to search for or recognize its actual tag. (e.g., part of the vehicle's plate is obstructed by the next car's side-view mirror or bumper has bike rack) Note: If obstruction is evident but system captured at least 4 characters and you found the tag's Parent, register it in the system as the Child and assign the Parent.

Zero in both the Residential and Visitor Count. The interpreted tag number can be found in the SP Guard system but file shows the gate did not open. Registration date and time of the tag must be reviewed and checked.

This refers to vehicles with temporary plate numbers. Temp Tags are usually numeric in form with at least one letter, e.g., 22813C4, 22806V8, and consist an expiration date. In some communities, temporary tag numbers have to be forwarded to the HOA Office for owner identification. If owner is identified, temp tags can be added in the system and should be deleted once permanent license plate is already available.

Police cars, ambulance, and fire trucks. Auto-pass. Some communities have designated profiles in the SP Guard intended for emergency vehicles. If you find an emergency vehicle, add their tag into these designated profiles.

Vendors that are preauthorized by the HOA Office. Auto-pass. Check the image and when you found that the tag belongs to one of the preauthorized vendors, save the tag in their designated profiles. For example, Suburban Propane, search Suburban Propane in the designated HOA Office Address and save the tag in it.
System translated the tag of the vehicle that is in the Visitor's/Exit Lane. Check the tag image.

These are identified tags of residents who prefer not to use the LPR. We don't save these tags in the system. For your reference: In The Glen, the following tags should be opted out of LPR: MG8420K and 16607, including their child interpretations. These are tags from Jessica and Michael Sampere. They don't want to participate in using the system.
Any errors or specific issues that fail to recognize the tag and do not fall into any of the categories mentioned above. Provide description of the issue in a separate column.
